-- Nanosolar Hires IBM Veteran Steigele as COO After CEO Exits
-- B y   W i l l   W a d e
-- 2012-09-11T21:25:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-11/nanosolar-hires-ibm-veteran-steigele-as-coo-after-ceo-exits.html
Nanosolar Inc., a closely held
manufacturer of thin-film solar cells, hired Karl Steigele for
the newly created job of president and chief operating officer,
as Chief Executive Officer Eugenia Corrales left.  Nanosolar, based in  San Jose , California, didn’t give a
reason for Corrales’s departure in a statement today. Steigele
spent more than 30 years as an International Business Machines
Corp. executive.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
 wwade4@bloomberg.net  